{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_41","type":"agent_message","text":"I’m broadening the metadata one level, but still within the YARN client surface: all YARN `api.records.impl.pb.*` and `api.protocolrecords.impl.pb.*` no-arg constructors get guarded registrations behind `RecordFactoryPBImpl`. That matches how the library resolves record implementations by naming convention and avoids another one-by-one iteration for each protobuf record."}}
